Solution Q.17.21 Computing the volume of the histogram

Computes the volume of the histogram considering that the smallest
bar in one of the ends will limit the water from that side. Then we
move in the opposite direction to find the next bar that is taller,
which will limit the water from the other side. Repeat from the new
ends till i and j are equal:

                     *
                     *
           *         *
  i        *         *       *
+--->*     *         *       *       j
     *     *     *   *       *     *<--+
     *     *     *   *       *     *
     *     *     *   *       *     *
+---------------------------------------+
 0 0 4 0 0 6 0 0 3 0 8 0 2 0 5 2 0 3 0 0

                     *
                     *
           *         *
     i     *         *       * j
     *     *         *       *<---+end
     *     *     *   *       *     *
     *     *     *   *       *     *
     *     *     *   *       *     *
+---------------------------------------+
 0 0 4 0 0 6 0 0 3 0 8 0 2 0 5 2 0 3 0 0

                     *
                     *
           *         *       j
     i     *         *       *
     *     *         *       *
     *     *     *   *       *~~~~~*
     *     *     *   *       *     *
     *     *     *   *       *     *
+---------------------------------------+
 0 0 4 0 0 6 0 0 3 0 8 0 2 0 5 2 0 3 0 0
